  "text": "The HTTP filter chain registration and execution in Envoy follows this architecture:\n\n## Configuration Schema\nThe HttpConnectionManager protobuf (envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto) defines the configuration schema. The http_filters field (line 471) contains a repeated list of HttpFilter messages (defined at line 1339). Each HttpFilter specifies a filter name and typed configuration.\n\n## Registration Phase\nWhen HttpConnectionManagerConfig is instantiated (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h, line 127), it parses the HttpConnectionManager protobuf and uses FilterChainHelper template (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h, line 68) to process the filter list. FilterChainHelper.processFilters() iterates through each filter configuration and creates FilterFactoryCallbacks by invoking the registered filter factory. These callbacks are stored as FilterFactoriesList for later use.\n\n## Execution Phase\nWhen a new HTTP stream is created, FilterManager (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, line 638) is instantiated with the FilterChainFactory. FilterManager implements both FilterChainManager and executes filters at runtime. The createFilterChain() method of HttpConnectionManagerConfig (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc, line 780) invokes FilterChainUtility.createFilterChainForFactories() with the pre-built filter factories.\n\nFor each filter factory, the FilterManager applies the factory callback through applyFilterFactoryCb() (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, line 697). This creates a FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl instance (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, line 913), which is passed to the filter factory callback.\n\n## Filter Installation\nThe filter factory callback uses FilterChainFactoryCallbacks interface methods (envoy/http/filter.h, line 1224) to add filters:\n- addStreamDecoderFilter() - adds decoder-only filters\n- addStreamEncoderFilter() - adds encoder-only filters  \n- addStreamFilter() - adds bidirectional filters\n- addAccessLogHandler() - registers access log handlers\n\nFilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl wraps these calls to add filters to the FilterManager's decoder and encoder filter lists (lines 918-938), wrapping them in ActiveStreamDecoderFilter and ActiveStreamEncoderFilter for state tracking.\n\n## Key Integration Points\n1. ConnectionManagerImpl (source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h) creates HTTP streams and manages the overall connection\n2. DownstreamFilterManager (source/common/http/filter_manager.h, line 1094) specializes FilterManager with downstream-specific behavior like local reply handling\n3. The filter factory pattern allows plugins to register and provide filter implementations that are dynamically instantiated at stream creation time\n4. The FilterChainHelper template supports both static filter configuration and dynamic configuration discovery via ECDS"
}

